Executive-Incident-Brief.md

Executive Summary: On April 21, we successfully contained a "Credential Stuffing" attack.
Impact: No customer data was exfiltrated. 12 accounts were temporarily locked.
Legal/Regulatory: This event falls below the "Notifiable Breach" threshold for HIPAA/PDPA, but we have documented the response for our annual audit.
Next Step: Implementing a "Phishing Simulation" for the accounting department to harden the human element.
